</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9AFF832E19E84FA3E2FDE6" authority="G. R. Waterhouse, 1845" authorityName="G. R. Waterhouse" authorityYear="1845" box="[383,938,609,634]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Ormiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832E19E84FA234FDE6" box="[383,636,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Ormiscus variegatus</emphasis>
G. R. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B45FF9AFF832DAFE84FA3E2FDE6" author="Waterhouse, G. R." box="[713,938,609,634]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" pagination="19 - 41" refId="ref20701" refString="Waterhouse, G. R. 1845. Descriptions of Coleopterous Insects collected by Charles Darwin, Esq., in the Galapagos Islands. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 16: 19 - 41." type="journal article" year="1845">Waterhouse, 1845</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36B4FF9AFF832FA6E88CA468FCA6" blockId="28.[192,1440,673,826]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832FA6E88CA189FD26" bold="true" box="[192,449,673,697]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9AFF832EAFE88FA276FD26" box="[457,574,674,697]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Ormiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832EAFE88FA276FD26" box="[457,574,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Ormiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9AFF832CF6E88FA40AFD25" authorityName="Wollaston" authorityYear="1861" box="[912,1090,674,698]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Trigonorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832CF6E88FA40AFD25" box="[912,1090,674,698]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Trigonorhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the quadrate rostrum. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9AFF832D60E8EFA2C2FD45" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1876" box="[518,650,706,730]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Eusphyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832D60E8EFA2C2FD45" box="[518,650,706,730]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Eusphyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the antebasal transverse pronotal carina that is incapable of reaching the elytra base, and by the pronotal hind angles that are not projecting laterad the elytral humerae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D37FF9AFF832E5BE92FA1FAFC86" box="[317,434,770,793]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Ormiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAA6FF9AFF832E5BE92FA1FAFC86" box="[317,434,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Ormiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from most other anthribids by having separate lobes on the 3 
<superScript id="7C109BFCFF9AFF832FA9E90DA097FCB0" attach="left" box="[207,223,800,815]" fontSize="6" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">rd</superScript>
tarsomeres, notched eyes, small size, and by the quadrate rostrum.
</paragraph>
